Ewout:

Thinks for the tip.  I ran across Softy myself today.  I&#39;m still trying
to figure out whether using Softy with Jerome will permit me to attempt
a more logical remap of the QWERTY keyboard for QS or whether this is
part of the driver?  As a beginner at this, I&#39;m lost.  How does one tell
the computer that you want to press two keys, one after the other, and
that the screen should then display the appropriate QS character?

I would like to get more texts on the Read_Alphabet site, but I don&#39;t
want to do this until we get a more logical mapping in place.  No point
in doing it with the old mapping, which I find horrendous!  However, I
would like to have a program that would transliterate (?) from the new
mapping back to the old so that people would be able to copy files from
the Shavian mapping to a new Jerome mapping and have them still make
sense.  I am handicapped in this by being, at best,  semi-computer
literate.  I just don&#39;t have time to spend learning all this stuff.  At
least, not presently.

By the way, I went to your website, which I had not seen.  I appreciate
your hard work, and it&#39;s good to learn a little more about you.  You are
an interesting person.  Thanks to the internet, we can get to know each
other.  I have sort of thought of Dutch as being a germanic language
somewhat intermediate between English and German.  Is this inaccurate?
Your comment that you had not learned too much German in school
surprised me.  I guess I thought German would be easier for a Dutch
speaker to learn than it is for an English speaker.

 I have also spent time learning Esperanto.  Can you make your computer
show the accents properly.  Their use of &quot;x&quot; after a letter needing an
accent just looks so stupid to me.  I expect it is much more difficult
to find Esperanto speakers here in the U.S. than it is in Europe.

One last point, when I tried connecting to Read_Alphabet on your site,
the link did not work.  I am wondering now whether the underline between
the two words was included as it must be?

Paige Gabhart



